cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper deals with computational techniques to detect and analyze geographic variation in language, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses statistical methods and machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with analyzing large datasets, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Data) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
